1 Influential in advancing the CNMI' s standing throughout the Pacific region,
2 Diego Tenorio Benavente has worked to strengthen ties between island
3 governments and promote cooperative development. In addition to his service in
4 the Legislature, he also served one term from 2002-2006 as Lieutenant Governor
5 of the CNMI under the administration of Former Governor Juan Nekai Babauta,
6 where his leadership extended to the executive branch and reinforced his reputation
7 for integrity and dedication. Following his term, he was once again elected to the
8 House of Representatives, serving in the Sixteenth and Seventeenth Northern
9 Marianas Commonwealth Legislatures, where he continued to champion tourism,
10 economic development, and resource management. Today, he continues to serve
11 the region as a member of the Board of Directors of the Pacific Islands
12 Development Bank and, since 2018, as the Honorary Consul of the Federated States
13 of Micronesia to the CNMI, roles through which he champions the growth and
14 prosperity of island communities.
15 Exceptional in his accomplishments beyond the halls of government, Diego
16 Tenorio Benavente is an avid fisherman who has worked to persevere and has
17 earned victories in several fishing derby categories, including twice being named
18 Grand Champion of the annual Saipan International Fishing Tournament. Many of
19 these marine activities begin at the Smiling Cove Marina on Saipan, a central harbor
20 and landmark for the fishing community. Smiling Cove has long been a gathering
21 place for fishermen, families, and visitors alike, and it is fitting that this landmark
