2 of the sea. His life-long membership in the Saipan Fishermen's Association reflects
3 his deep connection to the maritime traditions of the Commonwealth and his
4 commitment to preserving them for future generations. Through both competition
5 and advocacy, he has helped foster pride in the CNMI' s fishing heritage and
6 inspired others to carry it forward.
7 Generous with his time, wisdom, and compassion, he has been a source of
8 guidance and support for countless individuals across the Commonwealth. As a
9 devoted husband, loving father, proud grandfather, supportive brother, and caring
10 uncle, Diego Tenorio Benavente is admired not only for his public service but for
11 the humility and kindness that define his character. These personal qualities have
12 made him as beloved in private life as he is respected in public life, creating a legacy
13 built on both achievement and service to humanity.
14 Owing to the Diego Tenorio Benavente's long-standing legacy as a
15 distinguished public servant and devoted fisherman, it is only fitting that the
16 relevant Smiling Cove Marina bears his name. This designation will serve as a
17 lasting tribute to his leadership, his contributions to the Commonwealth, and the
18 example he has set for future generations. By renaming Smiling Cove Marina, as
19 the "Diego T. Benavente Smiling Cove Marina," the Delegation affirms its
20 recognition of a lifetime dedicated to service, community, and the enduring values
21 that bind the Commonwealth together.
