1 SECTION 2. AMENDMENT.
2 Notwithstanding any CNMI laws, regulations, or rules to the contrary, Title
3 1. Government, Chapter 4. Honoring Special Persons, Article 2. Naming of Public
4 Buildings, Roads and Facilities: Saipan, is hereby amended to add a new Section
5 430.02 that shall read as follows:
6 "Diego T. Benavente Smiling Cove Marina.
7 The designated harbor/marina located between the "American Memorial
8 Park" and the "Eloy S. Inos Peace Park" in Puerto Rico on Saipan,
9 Commonwealth of the Northern Mariana Islands, shall be henceforth known
10 as the "Diego T. Benavente Smiling Cove Marina."
11 SECTION 3. ADMINISTERING AUTHORITY.
12 The Department of Lands and Natural Resources, through the Division of
13 Fish and Wildlife, shall continue to administer the Smiling Cove Marina facility,
14 which shall be henceforth known as the "Diego T. Benavente Smiling Cove
15 Marina".
16 SECTION 4. SEVERABILITY.
17 If any provision of this Act or the application of any such provision to any
18 person or circumstance should be held invalid by a court of competent jurisdiction,
19 the remainder of this Act or the application of its provisions to persons or
20 circumstances other than those to which it is held invalid shall not be affected
21 thereby.
